# Testing

## Structure
- Unit: no DB, no network — test logic in isolation
- Integration: real services — verify system behavior
- Test names describe behavior: "should return 404 when user does not exist"
- Each test tests ONE behavior — Arrange → Act → Assert

## Writing tests
- Factories for test data, not raw objects
- Mock at boundaries, not internal functions
- If you need 3+ mocks, code under test does too much — refactor

## Coverage
- 80%+ on business logic
- Don't chase 100% on config/types
